Run live animated hero in laptop screen on mobile and tablet

The mobile/tablet path previously used a clip-path masked video so the
hero video played but the eyebrow, headline and CTA were missing — only
desktop got the full live hero. This collapses both paths onto a single
iframe-based component:

- LaptopScreenIframe now mounts on every viewport (the lg+ matchMedia
  gate is gone). It is still IntersectionObserver-gated so the second
  React app + GSAP boot only happens once the card approaches the
  viewport.
- LaptopScreenVideo and its clip-path bbox helpers are removed.
- The mobile inline media block uses LaptopScreenIframe for the
  websites slide, behind the laptop's alpha hole with the same matrix3d
  perspective mapping as desktop.

Verified on 390 / 768 / 1440 px: video plays, eyebrow + headline + CTA
animate in and settle, no extra iframe mounts on desktop.
